Martial Power																CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																																																							PRESPELLTYPE:1,Initiator=1	PRESTAT:1,CON=13																		SERVESAS:ABILITY=Feat|Combat Expertise	DEFINE:MartialPowerAttackPenalty|0	DEFINE:MartialPowerTempHP|0	DEFINE:MartialPowerShieldTempHP|0	DESC:You can choose to take a -%1 penalty on attack rolls and combat maneuver checks to gain %2 temporary hit points. This bonus is increased by half (50%%) [to %3] when you are using a shield of any kind. You can only choose to use this feat when you declare that you are making an attack or a full-attack action with a melee weapon, or when you are initiating a maneuver. The penalty to attack rolls and temporary hit points gained from use of this feat last until the start of your next turn. Special: Martial Power can be used in place of Combat Expertise to qualify for a feat, prestige class, or other special ability. You can take both this feat and Combat Expertise.|MartialPowerAttackPenalty|MartialPowerTempHP|MartialPowerShieldTempHP																																																																																																																																																																																																															BONUS:VAR|MartialPowerShieldTempHP|MartialPowerTempHP*1.5	BONUS:VAR|MartialPowerAttackPenalty|floor((BAB+1)/2)	BONUS:VAR|MartialPowerTempHP|2*floor((BAB+1)/2)																						SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Martial Training I										SORTKEY:Martial Training 1	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																					PREMULT:1,[PREATT:3],[PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Martial)=3]																																																																									DEFINE:HighestInitiatorLVL|0													DESC:Select a martial discipline. The associated skill for this discipline is now a class skill. Your martial initiator level maneuvers granted by this feat (and subsequent Martial Training feats) is equal to half your character level + your attribute modifier that modifies your chosen discipline for use with this discipline (example, Dexterity for a discipline that uses Acrobatics), not to exceed your character level. Likewise, your initiation modifier is the attribute modifier that effects the associated skill of this chosen discipline (for example, Charisma if the discipline uses Diplomacy). You may select any two maneuvers from the 1st level maneuvers from this discipline, and you may ready one of your maneuvers for use. You may recover one maneuver by expending a full round action to recover it. Special: If you ever gain levels in a martial adept class or possess them previously, these maneuvers continue to use their own initiator level and recovery method, independent of your martial adept level. Those wishing to add new maneuvers from a discipline that is already available to their class should instead select the Advanced Study feat instead										ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Martial Training ~ Initiating																																																				ADD:SPELLCASTER|Martial Training	ADD:SPELLCASTER|Martial Training Stances																																																					BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingInitiatorLVL|min(TL,TL/2+MartialTrainingStatBonus)	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingManeuversKnown|2	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingManeuversReadied|1	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingFeatManeuverLevel|1	BONUS:VAR|HighestInitiatorLVL|MartialTrainingInitiatorLVL|TYPE=NoStack	SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Martial Training II										SORTKEY:Martial Training 2	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Martial Training I												PREMULT:1,[PREATT:5],[PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Martial)=5]																																																																																										DESC:You may select two new maneuvers and one stance from your chosen discipline of up to 2nd level, and you may ready an additional maneuver. You must meet the minimum initiator level to select any maneuver.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingManeuversKnown|2	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingStancesKnown|1	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingManeuversReadied|1	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingFeatManeuverLevel|1																			SOURCEPAGE:p.23
Martial Training III										SORTKEY:Martial Training 3	CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Martial Training II												PREMULT:1,[PREATT:7],[PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Martial)=7]																																																																																										DESC:You may select an additional new maneuver from your chosen discipline of up to 3rd level, plus one new stance, and you may ready an additional maneuver. You may also trade out any one maneuver from your chosen discipline you know and replace it with a different maneuver from that discipline of up to 2nd level. You must meet the minimum initiator level to select any maneuver.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingManeuversKnown|1	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingManeuversReadied|1	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingStancesKnown|1	BONUS:VAR|MartialTrainingFeatManeuverLevel|1																			SOURCEPAGE:p.23
